      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical R19.2 is a commercially validated solver with documented QA procedures, regression test suites, and ISO 9001-certified development processes. FDA in-house scripts were version-controlled under Git with peer-review prior to release."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed via comparison against analytical beam-theory solutions for simple cantilever geometries. Residual norms monitored to convergence tolerances of 1e-6 for all load steps."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed across three refinement levels (coarse, medium, fine). Peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness changed by less than 2% between medium and fine meshes, confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) employed with double-precision arithmetic. Energy balance checked at each load increment; no numerical instabilities observed across all 11 construct simulations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Model setup checklist documented and independently reviewed by a second analyst. Boundary condition application and material property assignment verified against pre-approved simulation protocol prior to each run."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic constitutive model adopted for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V). Small-displacement assumption justified given measured construct displacements remain below 5 mm at failure load. Frictional contact at screw-block interface modelled with Coulomb friction coefficient calibrated from literature."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certified material certificates for each lot. Screw geometry reconstructed from micro-CT scans with voxel resolution of 20 µm. Polyaxial head torque values set per manufacturer assembly instructions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 physical constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Sample size exceeds ASME V&V 40 minimum recommendation for medium model risk. Constructs drawn from a single production lot to minimise inter-specimen variability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single load configuration (compression-bending at 5° offset) per ASTM F1717. Variability in loading rate and environmental conditions (ambient laboratory temperature) not systematically characterised. This factor falls below required level; risk accepted by the assessment team pending future multi-condition testing."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
